      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 14,
      "message": "If you have integrated vvp/documentation with the doc project (instructions here http://docs.onap.org/en/amsterdam/guides/onap-developer/how-to-use-docs/include-documentation.html#setup-project-repositories-s) you can just reference this file within vvp/documentation/docs/index.rst, and you do not need any of the conf.py or requirements.txt files at lower levels.\n\nAny patch set with files matching ANT pattern docs/**/*.rst will trigger a doc-{stream}-verify-rtd.   A merge of a patch set with files matching the pattern will trigger an update at read the docs.  Both verify and merge/publish at RTD create a file structure that includes all integrated project/repositories as git submodules and run sphinx_build on the doc project master index.",
